lementation of the electronic research administration eRA project at the NIH The Project Management Team comprises Advocates who represent business and functional area end users and policy makers and Branch Chiefs reporting to the eRA Implementation and Operations Manager In all of its undertakings the Project Management Team receives broad oversight and advice from the eRA Steering Committee For each area of focus the eRA Advocate teams with an Analyst and developers to translate user requirements into software design specifications Together they formulate implementation plans that they present to the eRA Project Management Team for approval Presentation of each plan to the entire team identifies areas of overlap requiring wider participation in planning and decision making During the subsequent development phase the Advocate and Analyst work cooperatively to provide guidance and oversight to the development contractor and subcontractors Throughout planning development testing and execution the eRA Office of Project Management provides additional project oversight monitoring and coordination The Office of Project Management works closely with the Project Management Team to determine the priorities for development activities tracking them against the Project Management Plan By creating a functional architecture for eRA the System Architect provides a roadmap to Analysts and developers for migrating eRA stovepiped systems into an integrated architecture The Operations Ops team manages the eRA technical infrastructure and provides monitoring tuning and problem resolution The Ops team deploys new software and hardware with the assistance of the Systems Quality Assurance and Interfaces Branch and the User Support Branch USB The USB also provides support and information to users of the eRA systems The Communications and Outreach Branch documents and communicates issues decisions and actions for the project through minutes newsletters the eRA website and other vehicles It also provides training and system documentation Current and future year project plans and budget projections are submitted through the Project Management Team Steering Committee and Information Technology Board of Governors BOG to the Funding Advisory Review Board FARB for final review prioritization among competing NIH enterprise system requirements and funding aboutera feedback help cfm Feedback and Help http www nih gov about access htm Accessibility http www nih gov about privacy htm Privacy
